blog.description:
Hello, I'm tinsnip.

Feeling rather ineffable these days. Expect a great deal of Good Omens.

Other interests: Star Trek. (Primarily DS9 and Cardassians.)
Pratchett. Wodehouse.
Cats. The Doctors Whom. Science. Cute things. Life truths. Pixels. And spiders, sometimes, so keep that in mind.

I post fic on AO3. It's quite good - you should have a look.

My work with Vyc on a Kardasi conlang is here.

Cardassian meta is found mostly under cardassians or kardasi.

If you enjoy my fanfic, why not buy me a coffee?

summary: Look, listen, I just can’t, I can’t afford to fall in love with Tennant as Crowley. I’m already head over heels gonzo for Sheen...
body:
Look, listen, I just can’t, I can’t afford to fall in love with Tennant as Crowley. I’m already head over heels gonzo for Sheen as Aziraphale.

It’s just that I’ve managed to avoid the mad love for Tennant that pervades this website. I started watching Doctor Who and he’s not my favourite, for God’s sake, and I’ve had a perverse little pride in that, and now–

Now–

He’s so good as the character and apparently he’s a really nice person and I just can’t–

It’s a matter of pride!
